      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BORN TO ENTERTAIN (9) finished second last start, beaten 16 metres at Bathurst over 1730m. Talented and has plenty of upside. Hard to know where he gets from this slightly awkward draw. Facing a tougher assignment but he is up to the task. THE MYTEE DUCK (8) has been knocking on the door for a while then went close again last time over 1730m at Bathurst, finishing third and just 18 metres from the winner. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. Stepping up a level this time but on his best form he is capable of another big performance. JUSTAQUICKSCHOONER (4) has to come into calculations on the back of some strong recent form, most recently when third at Coolamon over 1760m. Must be included. LUCKY GIRL (6) faces the starter for the first time. By Yankee Rockstar and hails from the Josh Turnbull stable. Was not far away in a recent trial. Sure to prove very hard to beat.",
